        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-05T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-05T06:30:00-05:00" n="243"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1173</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-05T11:30:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1914, 11:30 a.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>992. Your November 3, 8 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d243fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> informs me to-day that
                    state of war exists between Great Britain and Turkey. The Turkish Embassy left
                    this morning. I have taken charge of Ottoman interests and directed the Consul
                    General to inform the consuls in the United Kingdom accordingly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
